author: @chris-graham
text: "at a typical DE you can trust like 10%"  welcome to champcar racing ;)  5:58 - when you go to pass someone, try to squeeze as close to the car as possible. it compromises their corner entry and prevents them from overtaking you via. over/under. essentially you make them go so deep into the corner that thay're forced to turn sharper than you. also when they hit you (and eventually they will), a small tap from a few inches is much less damage than a large impact from a few feet.
